737
00:43:19,096 --> 00:43:21,432
Mm. Yes, we had help then.

738
00:43:22,516 --> 00:43:23,350
But

739
00:43:24,768 --> 00:43:27,187
can't we just try
to do it on our own this time?

740
00:43:31,317 --> 00:43:32,151
Hmm?

741
00:43:38,824 --> 00:43:39,950
[music fades]

742
00:43:41,785 --> 00:43:44,997
I've been thinking
about how we can kidnap Gun-woo's mother.

743
00:43:47,124 --> 00:43:48,959
[sinister music playing]

744
00:43:49,043 --> 00:43:52,171
The four of them
are serving life sentences in prison.

745
00:43:52,254 --> 00:43:53,380
They all would be good.

746
00:43:53,464 --> 00:43:56,300
They've got a grudge against Kim Gun-woo
and his friend, Hong Woo-jin.

747
00:43:56,800 --> 00:43:58,594
If we can get them out of prison,

748
00:43:59,261 --> 00:44:02,014
we'll get relentless bloodhounds
that will never give up.

749
00:44:02,097 --> 00:44:03,474
Can we control them?

750
00:44:05,267 --> 00:44:06,518
I see why you're concerned.

751
00:44:06,602 --> 00:44:09,104
They won't have any choice
but to rely on us

752
00:44:09,188 --> 00:44:11,273
since they'll be wanted criminals.

753
00:44:11,357 --> 00:44:13,108
And if they help us get the job done,

754
00:44:14,109 --> 00:44:17,446
I'll throw a carrot and offer to help them
to escape to somewhere abroad.

755
00:44:17,529 --> 00:44:18,906
How much does that cost?

756
00:44:19,823 --> 00:44:22,284
100 million won. For each person.

757
00:44:25,829 --> 00:44:28,707
[sighs] Shitface.
That's fucking expensive.

758
00:44:28,791 --> 00:44:31,710
The profit's going to be
more than ten times the cost.

759
00:44:31,794 --> 00:44:33,629
You're full of shit.

760
00:44:37,508 --> 00:44:40,094
[sinister music builds]

761
00:44:52,314 --> 00:44:53,232
This one.

762
00:44:54,733 --> 00:44:56,318
The one I would've picked.

763
00:44:56,819 --> 00:45:01,532
There's a security company I always use
whenever I have VIPs visiting from abroad.

764
00:45:01,615 --> 00:45:03,784
The founders are
former presidential security agents,

765
00:45:03,867 --> 00:45:05,411
which means they're thorough.

766
00:45:05,494 --> 00:45:08,455
But recently, their sales director
and their CEO had a falling out.

767
00:45:08,539 --> 00:45:12,751
By default, their hired hands
haven't been paid for a very long time.

768
00:45:14,002 --> 00:45:14,878
So what?

769
00:45:14,962 --> 00:45:17,881
There's a small risk
of things not going our way.

770
00:45:17,965 --> 00:45:21,093
Well, especially because gangsters
and ex-cons are rough.

771
00:45:21,593 --> 00:45:24,513
So in case Ms. Yoon gets hurt,
things could get really messy,

772
00:45:24,596 --> 00:45:26,348
which isn't what we want.

773
00:45:26,849 --> 00:45:29,476
So I recommend we use them,

774
00:45:29,560 --> 00:45:31,520
even if it costs a little more extra.

775
00:45:33,063 --> 00:45:37,693
[sighs] Shit, another way
to get extra funds? Just handle it.

776
00:45:40,279 --> 00:45:43,782
During jobs like these there are
all sorts of variables that might happen.

777
00:45:44,366 --> 00:45:48,912
That's why… you should
go with a bloodhound who has our back.

778
00:45:49,413 --> 00:45:51,874
That's a golden rule when I'm working.

779
00:46:01,842 --> 00:46:02,843
No mistakes.

780
00:46:02,926 --> 00:46:03,844
[music fades]

781
00:46:04,845 --> 00:46:06,388
Thanks for the payment.

782
00:46:12,728 --> 00:46:13,604
Hmm.

783
00:46:14,396 --> 00:46:15,856
Will you get these for me?

784
00:46:17,608 --> 00:46:20,444
GASOLINE, DDNP, SALTPETER
NICHROME, DETONATOR, CELL PHONE

785
00:46:20,527 --> 00:46:21,653
[chuckles]

786
00:46:23,697 --> 00:46:26,325
There's no reason
to go this far, Sergeant Yun.

787
00:46:26,408 --> 00:46:28,869
I need to be ready, Mr. Lee.

788
00:46:28,952 --> 00:46:30,037
[chuckles]

789
00:46:31,121 --> 00:46:32,039
Well,

790
00:46:33,165 --> 00:46:34,249
trust what I do.

791
00:46:34,333 --> 00:46:36,084
I still need to be ready and prepared.

792
00:46:37,628 --> 00:46:39,296
[laughs]

793
00:46:40,047 --> 00:46:41,673
[thudding]

794
00:46:46,470 --> 00:46:48,347
[In-beom grunts]

795
00:46:55,437 --> 00:46:56,522
[ominous music playing]

796
00:46:56,605 --> 00:46:57,439
TAO TE CHING

797
00:47:00,859 --> 00:47:03,695
SWALLOW THIS AT 1 P.M. TWO DAYS FROM NOW
I'LL GET YOU OUT

798
00:47:16,291 --> 00:47:17,334
[music fades]

799
00:47:18,418 --> 00:47:20,921
[brakes squeal]

800
00:47:21,839 --> 00:47:23,715
[tense music playing]

801
00:47:40,566 --> 00:47:41,650
[car lock beeps]

802
00:47:43,986 --> 00:47:44,987
[exhales]

803
00:47:45,946 --> 00:47:47,322
[sighs with relief]

804
00:47:50,158 --> 00:47:51,243
[music fades]

805
00:47:52,286 --> 00:47:54,746
[man] With this last one,
you have eight in total.

806
00:47:54,830 --> 00:47:55,747
It should be good.

807
00:47:55,831 --> 00:47:57,499
- [Gun-woo] Thank you.
- [Woo-jin] Gun-woo!

808
00:47:57,583 --> 00:47:59,209
- You outside?
- [Gun-woo] Yeah.

809
00:48:01,295 --> 00:48:03,213
Adik's team is leaving today.

810
00:48:03,714 --> 00:48:06,425
Yet, Adik has disappeared.
He's gone missing.

811
00:48:06,508 --> 00:48:07,551
[sighs]

812
00:48:08,135 --> 00:48:10,554
UZBEK BOXER MISSING AFTER TITLE FIGHT.
POLICE INVESTIGATING.

813
00:48:10,637 --> 00:48:11,847
[breathes heavily]

814
00:48:11,930 --> 00:48:12,973
[tense music playing]

815
00:48:13,056 --> 00:48:14,224
I have a bad feeling, Woo-jin.

816
00:48:14,808 --> 00:48:17,728
I think those assholes are behind this.

817
00:48:22,441 --> 00:48:23,483
[music fades]

818
00:48:36,496 --> 00:48:37,664
[suspenseful music playing]

819
00:48:37,748 --> 00:48:38,999
[camera whirs]

820
00:49:04,441 --> 00:49:05,943
Sir, this is the job?

821
00:49:08,153 --> 00:49:09,154
It's just,

822
00:49:09,655 --> 00:49:11,490
why do we have to stoop so low?

823
00:49:12,783 --> 00:49:14,242
We're trained to protect.

824
00:49:14,326 --> 00:49:16,411
[man 1] How does it help to say this now?

825
00:49:17,537 --> 00:49:18,538
We agreed to do it.

826
00:49:20,540 --> 00:49:23,168
Don't you understand
we're about to go under?

827
00:49:23,669 --> 00:49:25,837
We need to pay the other guys too.

828
00:49:26,421 --> 00:49:28,465
Hey. They trusted us.

829
00:49:29,049 --> 00:49:31,385
They worked hard and what did they get?
Broken bodies.

830
00:49:31,468 --> 00:49:33,887
- Yes, I know that, of course, but--
- [man 2] Jin-nam.

831
00:49:34,972 --> 00:49:37,849
Stay in the car. We'll handle it.

832
00:49:38,558 --> 00:49:42,145
[sighs] Mr. Jang,
we can't finish the job with two.

833
00:49:43,438 --> 00:49:44,731
Let's give it a go.

834
00:49:44,815 --> 00:49:46,817
[tense music playing]

835
00:49:52,864 --> 00:49:56,284
[laughs]

836
00:49:56,368 --> 00:49:58,328
[beeping]

837
00:49:58,412 --> 00:49:59,413
[man 3] Bingo.

838
00:49:59,496 --> 00:50:00,330
FRONT DOOR

839
00:50:00,372 --> 00:50:01,206
[lock clicks]

840
00:50:07,921 --> 00:50:09,339
[outgoing call ringing]

841
00:50:10,924 --> 00:50:11,967
Yes?

842
00:50:12,551 --> 00:50:13,635
You can go in.

843
00:50:26,273 --> 00:50:27,274
[Jang] Let's do it.

844
00:50:29,526 --> 00:50:31,528
[dramatic music playing]

845
00:50:48,754 --> 00:50:50,881
[device whirs]

846
00:50:50,964 --> 00:50:52,966
[tense music playing]

847
00:51:12,486 --> 00:51:15,947
[breathes deeply]

848
00:51:40,597 --> 00:51:45,602
[So-yeon gasps, struggles]

849
00:51:51,108 --> 00:51:53,652
- [tense music builds]
- [muffled screaming]

850
00:51:58,573 --> 00:51:59,616
[music fades]

851
00:52:01,243 --> 00:52:02,536
Oh, Mom!

852
00:52:02,619 --> 00:52:04,204
[dramatic music playing]

853
00:52:04,287 --> 00:52:05,789
[both grunt]

854
00:52:08,500 --> 00:52:10,460
- [Woo-jin] Gun-woo!
- [Gun-woo] They're taking her.

855
00:52:12,045 --> 00:52:12,879
- My mom!
- Mom!

856
00:52:12,963 --> 00:52:14,965
- [Jang] Don't fight. I will.
- [man] It's my job.

857
00:52:18,802 --> 00:52:21,680
Shit! You fucker!

858
00:52:23,723 --> 00:52:24,641
[man groans]

859
00:52:26,601 --> 00:52:28,186
[man grunts, yells]

860
00:52:29,563 --> 00:52:32,524
[both grunting]

861
00:52:33,108 --> 00:52:34,192
[groans]

862
00:52:36,069 --> 00:52:38,572
[all grunting]

863
00:52:48,081 --> 00:52:49,958
- [Gun-woo] Woo-jin.
- What is it?

864
00:52:50,041 --> 00:52:51,835
- I've gotta go.
- What?

865
00:52:54,963 --> 00:52:56,089
Gun-woo, are you okay?

866
00:52:56,173 --> 00:52:57,424
[Gun-woo groans]

867
00:53:03,054 --> 00:53:04,264
[gasps]

868
00:53:05,223 --> 00:53:08,101
[panting]

869
00:53:08,852 --> 00:53:09,978
[grunts]

870
00:53:10,061 --> 00:53:13,940
[both straining]

871
00:53:19,237 --> 00:53:21,281
[both grunting]

872
00:53:33,251 --> 00:53:34,377
[groans]

873
00:53:34,461 --> 00:53:36,379
[both grunting]

874
00:53:45,180 --> 00:53:46,806
[groans]

875
00:53:54,981 --> 00:53:56,316
[Taser crackling]

876
00:53:58,693 --> 00:54:00,946
[all grunting]

877
00:54:02,197 --> 00:54:05,617
[groaning]

878
00:54:09,079 --> 00:54:09,996
[both straining]

879
00:54:10,080 --> 00:54:11,998
- [cries out] Ugh!
- [grunts forcefully]

880
00:54:14,417 --> 00:54:15,418
We've gotta go.

881
00:54:15,961 --> 00:54:17,003
[So-yeon groans]

882
00:54:17,629 --> 00:54:18,713
Agh!

883
00:54:19,547 --> 00:54:21,591
[straining]

884
00:54:21,675 --> 00:54:23,593
[Taser crackling]

885
00:54:23,677 --> 00:54:26,972
[all grunting]

886
00:54:27,055 --> 00:54:29,724
- [Taser crackling]
- [groaning]

887
00:54:31,726 --> 00:54:32,894
[grunts]

888
00:54:32,978 --> 00:54:34,938
[heaving]

889
00:54:35,021 --> 00:54:36,189
[both grunting]

890
00:54:36,773 --> 00:54:38,775
[both grunting]

891
00:54:57,919 --> 00:54:59,045
[Taser crackling]

892
00:55:11,016 --> 00:55:14,894
- Shit!
- [straining]

893
00:55:23,403 --> 00:55:25,113
[both straining]

894
00:55:36,708 --> 00:55:40,587
[Taser crackling]

895
00:55:42,005 --> 00:55:44,174
[Gun-woo groans]

896
00:55:45,342 --> 00:55:48,720
[Taser crackling]

897
00:55:48,803 --> 00:55:50,680
- [man groans]
- [bone cracks]

898
00:55:54,893 --> 00:55:56,561
- Oh, oh, oh!
- [man yells]

899
00:55:58,855 --> 00:55:59,773
[Gun-woo gasps]

900
00:55:59,856 --> 00:56:01,483
- [man groaning]
- [Jang] You okay?

901
00:56:01,566 --> 00:56:03,026
- [man] It hurts a lot!
- Gun-woo!

902
00:56:03,109 --> 00:56:05,153
[breathing heavily]

903
00:56:10,950 --> 00:56:12,869
[man groaning]

904
00:56:15,163 --> 00:56:17,248
[Jin] Come on, let's go. Let's leave now.

905
00:56:19,459 --> 00:56:20,543
[music fades]

906
00:56:20,627 --> 00:56:23,505
- [Woo-jin] You okay?
- [groans]

907
00:56:23,588 --> 00:56:26,591
- Here. Can you get up?
- No, my… My mom's there!

908
00:56:26,674 --> 00:56:29,052
- [Gun-woo panting]
- [tense music playing]

909
00:56:30,095 --> 00:56:31,805
[groaning]

910
00:56:31,888 --> 00:56:33,598
- [whimpering]
- Hold on, I've got you.

911
00:56:33,681 --> 00:56:35,558
[groans]

912
00:56:35,642 --> 00:56:38,228
[heaving]

913
00:56:38,311 --> 00:56:39,187
[engine revs]

914
00:56:39,896 --> 00:56:40,939
[Jin] Come on, let's go!

915
00:56:44,567 --> 00:56:45,402
Hey, stop!

916
00:56:46,236 --> 00:56:49,364
Get up! Let's go! Come on!

917
00:56:50,657 --> 00:56:52,659
[dramatic music playing]

918
00:56:53,910 --> 00:56:56,496
- [Jin] Drive faster! Floor it!
- [grunts]

919
00:57:14,514 --> 00:57:16,599
[panting]

920
00:57:16,683 --> 00:57:18,977
[grunts with frustration]

921
00:57:21,896 --> 00:57:24,774
- [groans]
- [exhales]

922
00:57:24,858 --> 00:57:30,905
[groaning continues]

923
00:57:36,453 --> 00:57:39,038
[brakes squeal]

924
00:57:48,381 --> 00:57:50,383
[tense music continues]

925
00:57:50,467 --> 00:57:53,178
[panting]

926
00:58:08,234 --> 00:58:09,277
[music fades]

927
00:58:09,360 --> 00:58:11,362
[dramatic music playing]

928
01:01:07,372 --> 01:01:08,373
[music fades]
